description: This table presents a comparison of FID (Fréchet Inception Distance) scores, a metric for evaluating the quality of generated images, across various sizes of DiT (Diffusion Transformer) and SiT (Sinusoidal Transformer) models.  The models are trained on ImageNet images with a resolution of 256x256 pixels.  The comparison includes baselines (DiT and SiT models without any additional techniques), models enhanced with REPA (a representation learning technique), and models enhanced with the authors' proposed method, ReDi.  The table illustrates the improvement in image quality achieved by ReDi across multiple model configurations, highlighting its effectiveness compared to the baseline and REPA.

description: This table presents a quantitative comparison of the proposed ReDi model with state-of-the-art generative models. The models are evaluated on the ImageNet dataset with images resized to 256x256 pixels, using the Classifier-Free Guidance technique.  Both the REPA method (a comparable method from recent literature) and the ReDi model utilize the SiT-XL/2 architecture as a baseline for fair comparison.  The metrics used for evaluation likely include FID (Fréchet Inception Distance), IS (Inception Score), Precision, and Recall, to assess the quality of generated images.

caption: Table 5: Performance of Modality Combination Strategies. FID scores on ImageNet 256×256256256256\times 256256 × 256 without CFG for DiT-B/2 with ReDi using Separate Tokens (SP) and Merged Tokens (MR).
description: This table compares the performance of two different methods for combining image and representation tokens in a diffusion transformer model.  The model, DiT-B/2 with ReDi, is used to generate images on the ImageNet dataset at a resolution of 256x256 pixels. The two methods are 'Separate Tokens' (SP) and 'Merged Tokens' (MR). The table shows the Frechet Inception Distance (FID) scores achieved by each method, indicating the quality of the generated images. A lower FID score signifies better image quality.
